
[1]diffident

   DIFFIDENT, a.

   1. Distrustful; wanting confidence; doubting of anothers power,
   disposition, sincerity or intention.

   Be not diffident of wisdom.

   Be diffident in dealing with strangers.

   2. Distrustful of ones self; not confident; doubtful of ones own power
   or competency.

   Distress makes the humble heart diffident.

   3. Reserved; modest; timid; as a diffident youth.
